# Java DTO Patterns

- Use Lombok to reduce boilerplate. Prefer `@Builder` for object creation.
- Keep new DTOs immutable after creation. Prefer final fields, constructor-based creation, or records when they fit the module.
- Do not introduce `Optional` fields in DTOs. Use nullable fields or explicit nested objects instead.
- Name inbound payloads `*Request`, outbound payloads `*Response`, and shared transfer objects `*Dto`.
- Keep DTOs as transport shapes only. Do not place service calls, repository access, or business rules inside them.
- Use `@Data` only when matching an existing mutable pattern that already exists in the module. Do not default to it for new DTOs.
- When updating legacy DTOs, move them toward immutable construction instead of adding more setters.
